==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cardiograph
<hw>car"di*o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kardi`a</grk> heart + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An instrument which, when placed in contact with the chest, will
register graphically the comparative duration and intensity of the
heart's movements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cardiographic</ent>⟦br⟧
